						<p>On the north wall of the Veṅkaṭēśa-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīrarājēndradēva: c. 1207-52.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription of which the date portion is lost, mentions Pārā-tiriyaṉ Aḻaga[ṉ] of Puḷḷamaṅgalam, Tambirāṉ-tōḻaṉ, an ascetic, and a Brahmadē[śa] in Vaikāvi-nāḍu.</p>						

